1) IVF. Normally several embryos are implanted so that 1 or 2 will take. Is the doctor considered a murderer for implanting 8 or so, knowing that most of those will croak? Is the mother a murderer for having this procedure? In the case where she does have multiple embryos that happen to make it and keeping all of them would kill all of them, is it murder to sacrifice the life of one of those so that the rest may live?<br>
<br>
2) Frozen embryos. Is it murder to dipose of those things if they have been in stasis for 15 years? You could argue that those are &quot;potential life&quot; or whatever, but they are just sitting there doing nothing and costing a fortune to maintain, and will most likely never be used. Would the pro-lifers pay the cost to maintain those since the &quot;parents&quot; may not be able to?<br>
<br>
