Now back to Tain.  Since your opinion narrows things, let's broaden them again.<br>
There really are more than 2 categories.<br>
<br>
Anti-Abortion<br>
Catholics: Not exactly sure the stance, but fairly close to Antiu Abortion/Extreme Pro-Life.<br>
<br>
Pro-Life:  very very very extreme instances where an abortion might be ok.  Most of the Christian establishment is here or more right.<br>
<br>
from here it gets cloudier...<br>
<br>
Pro Choice Limited:  Abortion ONLY to save the mothers life.<br>
<br>
Pro-Choice for mothers well being: Abortion to save her life, or to avoid the suffering of a baby who would be born VERY sick and probably die very young.  Rape case abortions are usually split here.  No numbers, just my guess.<br>
<br>
Pro Choice extreme:  Abortion is ok for any situation where the mother prefers it.<br>
<br>
Now... as I said, this is how I see the breakdown roughly.<br>
<br>
Many camps, many ideas.<br>
<br>
Tain fine... I will step into your trap.  I think abortion is ok in some cases.<br>
<br>
Life threatening to the mother/child:  I simply think it is more humane.  I hate to see any one suffer, and remember the same people who scream about cruel and unusual punishment when it comes to criminals are the ones condemning these women to exactly that.<br>
<br>
Rape:  This one is touchier.  If the rape wasn't bad enough... I cannot imagine telling any woman, &quot;You have been raped, now you have to wake up every day for the next 9 months with a glaring reminder of your rape, you must carry the seed of the rapist, and must let him/her out into the world.&quot;  You know they have linked aggressive behavior to a gene right?  This gene could be carried on, this child could grow up to cure aids, or kill 10 people, or anything in the middle.  <br>
<br>
No woman with this decision is going to come asking our opinions.  You start a topic to bait some sucker into slipping up so you can nail them... well rough topic to do it on.  <br>
