It's perfectly reasonable to find a certain behavior distasteful but recognize that it's beyond the scope of what the government should make illegal.  Like chewing gum: I have a weird prejudice against it, inherited from my mother, who was strangely zealous about our not ever chewing gum.  I find the habit nasty, and I'd prefer people didn't do it around me.  On the other hand, I think it should be legal.  By Tain's logic, this means that gum-chewing is ok with me.  Which it's not, really.<br>
But anyways, I'll call Tain's bluff: abortion is ok, any day of the week.  You might even convince me it was murder (which I don't really buy, but both sides of the argument have to get into some hand-waving), and it would still be ok.  It's an exception I'm perfectly willing to make, because it's a situation that's completely unique -- this woman has something GROWING IN HER ABDOMEN.  Freaky!  That one fact defies attempts at comparison, and makes attempts at blanket principles shudder. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=chimeraadabard>ChimeraaDaBard</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://den.mine.nu/~hecate/chim.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(8/26/03 9:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3499.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pro-Abortion</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>People are more concerned with the label than the act itself. That says a lot. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
